vim has different modes:

*Insert mode[ਕੌਈ ਵੀ text insert/edit ਕਰਨ ਲਈ ਇਸ mode ਵਿੱਚ ਜਾਨਾ ਪੈਂਦਾ use i to enter in this mode]

*Command mode[text copy,paste,ਤੇ ਕਦੇ ਕਦੇ visualisation mode ਵੀ use ਕਰ ਲੈਂਦੇ use esc button to enter in this mode]

*Extended comnand mode[ save   ਜਾ quit ਕਰਨ ਲਈ use esc button+ : to enter this mode]

*Visual mode

by default ਆਪਾ command mode ਚ ਹੁੰਦੇ। we can go in insert mode by i।

commands---

:q //quit

:! //forecfully

:s //save

:c //cut

:p //paste

:d //delete

:u //undo

:wqa//save and quit all tabs

://append after cursor

cntrl + t //redo

/search // ਏਦੇ ਨਾਲ search ਹੁੰਦਾ।

:

:

The general pattern for search and replace is:

:s/search/replace/

Replaces the first occurrence of 'search' with 'replace' for current line

:s/search/replace/g

e: //reach end of work

a://append at the end of line

a;//append after the cursor

i:// insert before the cursor

I://

show number line=set number or se nu.

remove number line=set number or se nonu.

go to specific line type line number

gg to go to start of file

shift+g or G to go to end of file

0 to start of line

$ to end of line

[num] cc //cut

[num] dd //delete

[num] yy //copy

x: Deletes the character at the current cursor position

dd: Deletes the line at the current cursor position

dw:
Deletes the word at the current cursor position

d$: Deletes to the end of the line from the current cursor position

J: Deletes the line break at the end of the line at the current cursor position 

(joins lines)

u: Undoes the previous edit command

a: Appends data after the current cursor position

A: Appends data to the end of the line at the current cursor position

r char: Replaces a single character at the current cursor position with char

R text:
 Overwrites the data at the current cursor position with text, until you press 

Escape
